overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. After
  an initial review, the agent identified several missing features and was
  tasked with implementing them. The agent systematically worked through a list
  of seven high and medium-priority items. This involved adding a 1-10 severity
  scale for tiredness with critical safety messaging, implementing detection and
  recommendations for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, integrating
  placeholder outbound links to relevant health resources, and refining the
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring with weighted activities.
  Additionally, the agent expanded the CSV export to include all flattened
  questionnaire data and introduced new questions for pain severity and chronic
  fatigue screening. Each feature required updates to data types, validation
  schemas, UI components, and PDF report generation logic, ensuring the
  application now meets a more robust set of functional and reporting
  requirements.
